text: One thing we can conclude for certain from this hearing: Kamala Harris and Corey Booker are running for president

text: It’s telling that none of the prosecutors questions are about the assault itself.
author: politicalwire

text: Republicans stick with the prosecutor asking question. Remarkable. I wonder if Jeff Flake doesn’t decide he’s going to ask his own questions.
author: politicalwire

text: Did Brett Kavanaugh perjure himself? That seems to be the question of the day.
author: politicalwire

text: Let’s not forget that Christine Blasey Ford was just 15 years old when this happened. That’s even more horrifying.
author: politicalwire

text: It’s clear from all commentary that Republicans are screwing this up. If they stick with the prosecutor after the break, they’re fools.
author: politicalwire

text: If Republicans push through the Kavanaugh nomination, I really think they’ll lose the Senate. They have a massive problem with women and it’s getting worse by the minute.
author: politicalwire

text: Christine Ford saying what she remembers most vividly is Kavanaugh and Judge’s laughter is the most damning moment of this hearing.
author: politicalwire

text: Taking a break might be the best thing for Republicans. They’re blowing this hearing big time. Even Fox News anchors think so. Trump must be steaming right now.
author: politicalwire

text: Someone needs to tell Grassley that yelling doesn’t help his side
author: politicalwire

text: Did anyone tell this prosecutor that a Senate hearing is not a trial? Not going well.
author: politicalwire

text: I’ll bet Trump is going out of his mind watching this on television right now. The GOP is totally blowing this.
author: politicalwire

text: Did anyone vet this prosecutor? She’s not coming across as I think the GOP hoped. The format isn’t her friend either.
author: politicalwire

text: I’m curious to see if Republicans continue with this prosecutor asking questions every other five minutes… this wasn’t thought out very well. I wouldn’t be surprised if some Republicans just ask their own questions
author: politicalwire

text: This questioning by a prosecutor is a total joke
author: politicalwire

text: What cowards they are to not ask their own questions. They are U.S. Senators…
author: politicalwire

text: I’m speechless after Christine ford’s statement. That was very powerful and impossible to think she’s not being truthful
author: politicalwire

text: It takes enormous courage to do what Christine Ford is doing. A reminder that she is under oath to tell the truth.
author: politicalwire

text: I read Christine Ford’s testimony ahead of time. But hearing it is something different entirely.
author: politicalwire

text: If there was live polling of those watching this hearing, I wouldn’t be surprised if the gender gap just widened by a few more points
author: politicalwire

text: Grassley is truly the worst person to be doing this. He’s doing his party no favors. No wonder they brought in outside counsel to actually do the questioning
author: politicalwire

text: If you listen to Grassley, it’s hard not to conclude this hearing is a total sham. There will be no attempt to get at the truth. It’s not surprising, but I must say it’s really disappointing.
author: politicalwire

text: Not surprising, but Grassley is setting the tone for a hearing that has nothing to do about finding out what really happened.
author: politicalwire
